Fig. 3
shows the associations between ambient ozone levels and outpatient visits for total RD by ozone metric and study period. During hot seasons, outpatient visits for total RD were significantly and positively associated with O3, 24 h avg above 30 ppb and with Ox above 40 ppb. During cold seasons, on the other hand, the risk was also statistically significant in associations with O3, 1 h max above 40 ppb, O3, 8 h max above 30 ppb, and Ox above 45 ppb. The O3, 24 h avg had a significant positive association with outpatient visits for total RD in cold seasons; however, this study, as we observed the effects of ozone levels at 75th percentiles, obtained a lower risk estimate for O3, 24 h avg than other ozone metrics on associating with outpatient visits of total RD (Table 2
).
